Speaker of the National Assembly has assured the country that Parliament through an initiative by the National Assembly will soon embark on the process of reconstituting the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission to seek a way on how to replace the commissioners who resigned or whether to appoint a completely new crop of commissioners and force the remaining three to resign. In a consultative conference organised by the Konrad Adenuaer, an international body that champions for democracy in Kenya, Senate Minority leader James Orengo and Senate Majority leader Kipchumba Murkomen maintained that parliament should be at the fore front in ensuring Kenya gets a credible commission that will oversee the 2022 general election.  